createMenuItems

public void createMenuItems(AbstractEditorPanel view,
                            java.util.Vector menus,
                            java.util.Vector menuItems)
Newly created views call this method of each plugin in turn. The default implementation does nothing, but most plugins will want to override it to add instances of javax.swing.JMenu and javax.swing.JMenuItem to the appropriate vectors. The menus and menu items can be created dynamically by the plugin, but the preferred way is to use the methods of the GUIUtilities class.
